%N A398014 Decimal expansion of -Sum_{k>=1} mu(k) * log(k) / k^2, where mu is the Möbius function.
%H A398014 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 381, Corollary 2.9.
%F A398014 Equals -zeta'(2)/zeta(2)^2 = (Sum_{k>=1} log(k) / k^2) / (Sum_{k>=1} 1 / k^2)^2.
%F A398014 Equals (12*log(A) - log(2*Pi) - gamma)/zeta(2), where A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962) and gamma is Euler's constant (A001620).
%e A398014 0.346494734701802213346160816867709151548899264204041...
%t A398014 RealDigits[(12 * Log[Glaisher] - Log[2*Pi] - EulerGamma)/Zeta[2], 10, 120][[1]]
